geometry"><Array as="points"><mxPoint x="859" y="880"/><mxPoint x="755" y="956"/><mxPoint x="755" y="956"/><mxPoint x="755" y="956"/><mxPoint x="755" y="1064"/><mxPoint x="755" y="1064"/><mxPoint x="755" y="1064"/><mxPoint x="874" y="1136"/></Array></mxGeometry></mxCell><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Bob Fischer, Brian Tomasik)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vdtu4zYQ%2FZWB0aJ24DiyknR3XfghF%2BWCertB1ttFEQcOLY0sdilSIKkoajb%2F3qHkayw%2FRfEMz8ycOYd8bUUYs1zYCxVha9A6OoLhcAhjzbgEqyDU7L%2BSPgoJk9z3%2BidQKC2iZ44FFP2pPz2FtrEqg9OOOziRBHBmTJ5mlisJYUI4A%2FAgY1qFCWfCwfQ%2F%2BdCHmOkpK1g5TfKUSbMM%2BMAkT5kwU6NSLBJml5HTVSRl1iKdngplq5IBCxNg67rcAIO70ib0HXOBQNOsw%2BYIrMNlUWS6oJEo4BINKF2BaTykdlmKVIMb%2Bt0mWE%2Fym4E4l2GF8QeEKs2U4XK%2BTqCzMkJCpJ%2B4qdCMZTJiQkmElDgWPXhaURg8P7lW3XF8yTC0dPCZiRxBxRXCmu1eBXaOxsIsLyF3ZdxBg5uDDeBronmawXcUxC%2FCnVb%2FEm59%2Bjr4K7g%2FGweXMCthjhI1s9jLyuVqMeJ2i6YDCnZBKls345gkpArrkmvCBYxj94doRrcCpefEUUYtMF3CjErEPOT03YXz4OrLfUAcaCYqhAL5PLFEHzEilBNbwp%2FqzQk1l0rTquGT9ytc3EJbaZr3UMWHKZtLbvMI4fzLOLjoUD9G5dmf3IYJyksmyjvU30wEQ3idSIAMVSbwBkWG0Sri9bxTV9DrnbqcAoWYIXVyTSt0EHWK169zvL5LClUuSRAxC23OxDmTP%2F6uNuVSj%2FdUOmiAPoB2Hw73wXUm8m0i59HWIK4X72TRjOdPJEvjnYTjxUSeT%2B0ynu4kLKfxaWabiK14v%2Be76MkHYrPItkO%2B57nYhxNqYiILLqJZPjfbOb%2FXOR%2F9KocJEePuCP6KcjJIodT7jCruELyFxoKH4vJs9A%2BwZ9TOGhlJ%