Wkb9IdoRrcCpWfEUUYtMF3ClErEPOT0uQ3nwdWX%2B4A40ExUCAXyWWKJPmJEKKfEhD%2FVmxNqJpUmFUDP%2BxUubqGpNM17qOLDlM0kt3mEcP5lFFy0qB%2Bj8uwPbsME5SUT5R3qv0wEA3gdS4AMVSbwBkWG0TLidbwTV9DrnLicAoWYInVyTSt0EHWK161zvK5LClUuSRAxC23OxDmT3%2F%2BuNuVSP%2BypdLAD%2BgCaXTjcB9cay7exnEUbg7hevON5M54%2FliyNtxI%2BzCfyfGqX8XQrYTGNTzPbRGzEux3fRY8%2FEptFthnyPc%2FFPh5TE2NZcBFN85nZzDmtcz75VQ4TIsbtEfwl5WSQQqn3GVXcIXhzjQUPxeXZ8B9gz6idNTKS%2FC%2BP%2FXWpRRsytDyd23Uls1BRkESI0r6zFB1n724xyHJrnJq5s4wJlbPyAB7cfl%2BBeMc%2BjBtDFZI0nezge627caMNRbQcpw8pMtncKcwWKYAUA2%2FtTdBr%2Foy1qUS5G25dFf%2BHQt4X4K5rGklzW0Lz7PNVazfmhpIc6Dbk2e1nOIKLOVYgrcaMrjnMtUl4tgd2XX%2F7eh3Rnm7cs4AwRDbLcTfWhlZrrF7vdAtt98W3ZzHrGq8hvd52g99I6%2FRyGMIx0EzqVjO6gklOEZo9lG47ZF5hB7XD4VVwuYfCdyaqQHYsBwyL0S35vjYV3NObwHSY7Glvy3sr4EfnO01XkXvTBjDkxnY0kvkMNqt%2FjNL2vGzWvmjD64%2BXH%2FDSWavx1qILbOoeqQHMgR68x7mdRzufudHN7deVJ%2FtQ%2FRjgRPh08daR2zl1YciRay8nVXAZ69XHsvH2E8XhBBM%3D" id="w1_2_5_6"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2ccc0;strokeColor=#c96a4a;fontColor=#5a2410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="883" y="239" width="236" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Meat-eater problem&lt;br&gt;(saved humans eat animals)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+7]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Michael Dickens, Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + meat_eater_problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The meat-eater problem: a dollar of human global health also buys decades of that person&#x27;s meat consumption, and factory farming it causes suffering the animal circle now counts. Each present-human org is charged an additive penalty — farmed-animal life-years caused per human DALY, times the suffering per factory-farmed life-year, times the animal&#x27;s welfare range. Under a heavy animal welfare range the penalty can exceed the human benefit, so saving human lives looks net-harmful. Only bites once animals count, so it requires animals_somewhat; and it is a near-term human-vs-animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans), where x-risk dominates and the meat bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 6 suffering_focused → 7 meat_eater_problem" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vmlz4kYQ%2FStdVFIBx8ZC5jCk%2BOADH7Vs1uUl2UoZFztILTTZ0YxqZmSZeP3f0yNxGvhAIdQ9r6%2F3enirhBixTNgrFWKlVzk9hX6%2FDyPNuASrINDsvzk95BLGme81mpArLcIXjjnkjYk%2FaU3akw5UjVUpdGru8FgSyIUxWZJariQEMWH1wIOUaRXEnAkH1ej60ICI6QnL2XwSZwmTZmnwgUmeMGEmRiWYx8wuLa2VJWHWIp2eCLWytsFkUYSay9kkUkFmMFyaOpAgsxP60KFUq6nApMh0wIIY2DpdboDBw9zG9BxxgUCNWJvNKViXDgtDcwwaqXtcogGlCzCNJ1QlS5CicEPvbYxlA34zEGUyKDD%2BgEAlqTKU5tqBzsoQCZFecVOgGctkyISSCAmNR9Th%2B6r7g5fvLlV3HF9TDCwdfGEiQ1BRgbAeVL0Au0RjYZrNIXNh3EGDm4X14GuseZLCNxQ0FoQHrf4l3PL07eDPwePFaHAN0znMUKKmRtbT%2BZIVGHK71aYjMh6DpNkUybhOElKBdc014QLSpOiL2oxuBErPqEcppcD0HKYUIuIBp%2BdjuBzcfHkcUA80EwVCjnwWW2ofdUQox9OYfy8nJ9RMKk0Mga73K1zdQ1VpqvdERScJm0lusxDh8stocFWjfIzK0k%2FcBjHKaybmD6j%2FMiH04W0sAVJUqcA7FCmGK4tX91ouoFdvOZ8chZgiZXJLI3QQpYvXKH28hnMKVCaJEBELbMbEJZM%2F%2Fi4m5VzPDkQ62gN9BNUGnByCq43l%2B1jOwq1CXC5ec5GM548lS6Idh7NFRZ5P6TKe7Dgsq%2FGpZhuLLXuj7jtrs0PdzNNtk%2B95ztZpUhJjmXMRTrOZ2fZplz7nfuHDhIhwtwR%2F1XISSK7UR4%2FC7hC8BccGT%2Fn1xfAfYC%2BonTRSovwvz71NqoVbNLQ8Wch1TbNAkZFIiNJ%2BkBQdZx82HKSZNY7N3EnGBMpJuQ9Pbr5vQH3HHowrQxUQNR3t4EfJu3HlGPJwVU7P7SlZ3UvMGjGAGAO%2FQ%2FWkGOxZp3vWaNfg%2FXg7yi1%2FwVJlYr4ff5MmO7Dtdrfp%2BfthaTsIcMueitbczqF68fmmtj%2FIFtdclHWMdtvzzxu7IS7uP8MpXC2wB9JqTGkxYqZNzNMDYTYZ%2B7GY1lnrvLkbZ0SDvnN3DsIQ2SzD%2FdBbZC%2Bhu932Dtr%2BzXlgspsiKSG97tkO5DcSC109hnAMVOMy1ZR2OPExRHOg47sSW0TYDXAxHN4Mrg909IMKC5A9swLDInQceCxVCY90qTAdxAfS2xHvGvjZCVfTLnOXYh%2BG3Ni6RlKvwWrxwyhtL%2BfVUljH8Pbz9Se81jdivNdoA07dLdeHBdCT97zYB6O99%2BTo7v7rWtQ9KP5pcGr4dHlZ0rrglIUhSW9cvRTBeWxGH8vK%2B%2F%2BKOxn7" id="w1_2_5_6_7"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eec2a8;strokeColor=#c65a2e;fontColor=#5a2a10;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="926" y="478" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Net-negative lives&lt;br&gt;(animal suffering dominates)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+7+8]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Benatar)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + meat_eater_problem + net_negative_animal_lives&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The net-negative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 6 suffering_focused → 7 meat_eater_problem → 8 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vllv40YM%2FitE0KJ2mjiS4tiJCz%2FkcA5sthtk0y6KONCOJcqa7mhGmBlFcbP57%2BVIvo8Hw7JIfrw%2Bkn7fizFhhbCXKsa93t7REfT7fXjSjEuwCiLN%2FpvQQylhWASe34ZSaRG%%2Bpdwa%2BubwZ%2BDx%2FOnwRWMJjBGiZpq3conM%2BpgzO1KmfZJeACS2lcF4ypJSBXWFdeEC0jNpC8qM7oWKD2mGuUUAtMTGJGLhEecng%2FgYnD95XFANdBMVAgl8nFqqXxUEaEcmVP%2Bve6cUGOpNLUYzrxf4fIOGkpTvocqOczYWHJbxAgXX54Gl02Kx6gi%2F8RtlKK8YmLygPovE0Mf3ocSIEeVC7xFkWM8l3gt78Q59FonTqdEIUZIkdxQCx1EreL5tY7nO6VIFZIIkbDIFkxcMPnj76pTTvV4h6f9LdD70PDhcBdccyg%2FhnIcryTiYvHa02C8YChZlmwoHE8z8gIKl%2FFsQ2GWTUA521SsyP1W4KTtLlWzzFdFgec5WbdNQQxlyUU8KsZmVadT65wGlQ4TIsHN