ative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 7 meat_eater_problem → 8 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vm1z4jYQ%2Fis7mXYKKSG2QyChw4e8kJc5rpfJpb3phAwn7DVWT5Y8khyH5vLfu7Ih4AAfGIx39ezus8%2BueN2LMGa5sBcqwr3%2B3uEhDAYDeNCMS7AKQs3%2Bm9NDIWGcB57fgUJpET1zLKDwJ8HkeNKbnEDDWJXBSdMdHksCOTMmTzPLlYQwIaw%2BeJAxrcKEM%2BGg%2FNMAfIiZnrCCzSdJnjJploYAmOQpE2ZiVIpFwuzScvxuSZm1SKcnQr1be5AisxP6kCXTaiowXdpOQKKdSJwxy59xUsFMBD2bMuMhCxNgq7S5AQZ3c5vQc8wFAhGyMptDsC4tFkWmBRqJRS7RgNIlmMYDqpalSIlwQ%2B9tghURvxmIcxmWGH9AqNJMGS5nKwc6KyMkRHrFq9SMZTJiQkmElNok2vD9vQvD5%2B8uVXccXzIMLR18ZiJHUHGJsGpYuwQ7R2Nhms8hd2HcQYPrhfXha6J5msE3FNQehDut%2FiXc6vT18M%2Fh%2FdnD8BKmc5ihRE1ct7P5Uh0YcVujaZ%2BMLZDUozIZxyQhlViXXBMuYBy7L6IZXQuUnhFHGaXA9BymFCLmIafnFpwPr77cD4kDzUSJUCCfJZboI0aEcnpN%2BPeqc0LNpNLUYjj1foWLW2goTfUeqPggZTPJbR4hnH95GF40KR%2Bj8uwTt2GC8pKJ%2BR3qv0wEA3gdS4AMVSbwBkWG0bvFa3vHLqDXPnY%2BBQoxRcrkmlroICoXz698PN85hSqXJIiYhTZn4pzJH3%2BXnXKuRzsi7W%2BB3oeGDwe74Jpj%2BTaWs6hWiMvF6yyS8YKxZGm84XC0qMgLKF3G0w2HZTUB1WwTUbP77cBZOz1is8jqpsDznK3XoSTGsuAimuYzU%2FfpVj4nQenDhIhxs4TgnXIakEKpjx6l3SF4C40NH4vLs9E%2FwJ5Ru9HISPK%2FPPXXpRbVZGh5uhjXlcxCRUYSIUr7YaToOPuw6SDLrXFq5m5kTKjcKA%2Fg0fX3FYh37MN4b6RCkqaTHfyodDfea0ERvZfTd6tMNrYKs0kK8OF3aByUTTn2e0GvCW%2BteohrW